+# Data Products v1.5.0 Publication
+
+Date: 2026-07-23
+
+## Published identity
+
+- GitHub Release: `data-products-v1.5.0`
+- Release ID: `358964637`
+- Published at: `2026-07-23T21:27:39Z`
+- Exact tag target and source commit: `7f325d254b68eb495204c01c075727ee34893e1f`
+- Source Pull Request: `#223`
+- Verified Pull Request head: `723238c55f9cc7a0b45c5b60acf27d2dfe51ae87`
+- Quality workflow: `#1229`
+
+The tag resolves exactly to the merged `main` commit above. The release is final, not a draft and not a prerelease.
+
+## Public assets
+
+| Asset | Size | SHA-256 |
+| --- | ---: | --- |
+| `SHA256SUMS` | 213 bytes | `54fceff7c0adb6147782343ffaef3c81544af8c33b969bcc375e6df9e6217ed8` |
+| `dacia-knowledge-base-data-products-v1.5.0.zip` | 45,690,085 bytes | `ebbac6c85a3dd49e73c6e6a9ecd4bc5453be4e58e64996d7e6953416fa34c779` |
+| `data-product-release-manifest.json` | 19,153 bytes | `4158bd12e8a338daa3e92805eb5a43c7c0ad12992746380f22d29f8822d3f414` |
+
+GitHub's recorded API digests match the independently calculated SHA-256 values for all three downloaded assets.
+
+## Release contents
+
+- 69 active configurations;
+- 18 independent comparison scopes;
+- 79 deterministic archive members;
+- four exact Sandero Eco-G 120 Expression/Journey states with manual or automatic transmission;
+- four dated official catalogue prices: 68,000 PLN, 73,600 PLN, 74,900 PLN and 80,500 PLN;
+- 16 directly proven configuration-level standard-equipment observations;
+- exact source-to-model, source-to-version and source-to-configuration relationships;
+- a dedicated Sandero Eco-G 120 automatic comparison scope;
+- explicit preservation of unproven packages and default Essential TCe 100 options as non-imports;
+- the full offline browser, complete equipment comparison and differences-only interface.
+
+## Browser verification
+
+The exact HTML extracted from the published release archive was exercised in Chromium. Filtering to Sandero produced four configurations with catalogue prices 68,000 PLN, 73,600 PLN, 74,900 PLN and 80,500 PLN. Selecting the two automatic variants produced a full 19-row comparison table; the “Pokaż tylko różnice” switch remained operational and all 19 rows were genuine differences. No JavaScript console errors occurred.
+
+## Verification
+
+All 15 source Pull Request workflows passed on the final source commit, including 716 tests, Windows, HTML, workbook, comparison, selection-export and versioned-release verification.
+
+The public assets were then downloaded again from the published GitHub Release and accepted by `data-product-release --verify`. Publication audit result: `PASS`.
+
+## Immutability
+
+The release assets and tag are immutable. Later corrections or extensions must use a new semantic version and must not replace or rewrite `data-products-v1.5.0`.
